The paper discusses the mathematical properties of deep learning, which are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. However, given the focus on representation learning and classification, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. Other relevant sub-categories include cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
